description.narrative: (Georgia): The Restoring Efficiency to Agriculture Production (REAP) activity supports the development of commercially sustainable and competitive enterprises in agriculture to increase incomes and employment in rural areas. REAP delivers firm-level investment and technical assistance to expand the operations of existing smallholder farmers and rural enterprises. The program also facilitates the entry of new agribusinesses and input suppliers, including machinery service providers, storage facilities, sorting/grading centers, and processors. REAP catalyzes commercial finance to the sector and expands sustainable linkages among service providers, producers, post-harvest enterprises and local consulting firms. With FY 2016 funds, as reflected in Georgia's Feed the Future Scale-up Plan, REAP will support the expansion of 30 privately-run machinery and farm service centers to provide access to fee-based machinery services, agricultural inputs, and demonstration plots for 35,000 farmers.
